result.execSummary:
The defendant Brent Alan Fenner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Brent Alan Fenner is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Brent Alan Fenner was found guilty of Illegal Shining of Deer, Elk, or Bear [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 29.314(3)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Froelich - Guilty plea to Count 1, 3 year revocation of privileges, minimum fine of $1,000, State would Dismiss Count 2.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights  DEF PLEADS GUILTY to Count 1.     Facts are correct.    COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS.    The court finds the defendant guilty and adjudicates defendant guilty of Count 1.  Court dismisses Count 2.  Court orders fine in the amount of $1,000.00 plus surcharges and fee, $1,713.00, one year to pay.  No jail, 3 year revocation of approvals and no reissuance of approvals for 3 years.  Appeal rights are given to defendant.

10:00 a.m.  Defendant Brent Alan Fenner in court.  Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Froelich - Defendant does not have an attorney, wishes to proceed without attorney.  Court reviews trial process with defendant.  Jury trial set for April 14, 2016.  Court reviews Defendant's right to have an attorney.  Rights are explained. Defendant understands rights. Defendant waives the right to have an attorney represent him.

Final pre-trial on March 29, 2016 at 09:45 am.
Jury trial - 12 person on April 14, 2016 at 08:30 am.

10:26 Defendant Brent Alan Fenner in court.  Rory Eoin O'Sullivan appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Previously the court addresses the courtroom re: rights as a group.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant.  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights.  Defendant has copy of complaint . Court reads charges and possible penalties.  Defendant waives reading of the complaint. Def pleas not guilty. Court rec/enter. OSullinvan: $1000 signature bond. Def has no objection.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for March 15, 2016 at 03:00 pm.
